caption: Even if it is between the branches, it is nice to see the Eiffel Tower. Nice view from afar.
Excellent viewpoint for the tower especially at 6pm when it starts to shine

Less busy and smaller than its neighbor "Place du Tertre", in Montmartre, this more intimate square has a lot of charm. There is an old Art Nouveau house, and above all a restaurant "Chez Plumeau", a former Auberge du Coucou. In addition, this charming square offers a beautiful view of the capital and the staircase of Rue du Calvaire.
Slightly quieter place next to Place du Tertre, perfect for enjoying a drink, occasionally listening to street musicians and enjoying the view.
